<TITLE> Iajuddin asks journalists to be impartial </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 24 (bdnews24.com)President Iajuddin Ahmed Thursday urged journalists to be impartial in writing and publishing news stories. The media are enjoying freedom in Bangladesh, he said. "I call upon our media people to maintain the ethics of journalism and bring out objective news impartially with a sense of obligation to the nation," Iajuddin said in his speech as chief guest to the re-launching ceremony of English daily The Bangladesh Today at Hotel Sonargaon. "Today, the mediaboth print and electronicare enjoying freedom of expression in Bangladesh," he said. The president said: "We should pay our sincere attention to circulating a responsible newspaper keeping national interest above." "I call upon the country's media personnel  to come forward materialising the hopes and aspirations of people," Iajuddin said. Speaking as special guest, law adviser Hassan Ariff said: "The caretaker system is a testimony to the failure of our political system." The ceremony was also addressed by Syed Shahabuddin Ahmed, chairman of the newspaper's editorial board, and Mahmud ur Rahman Choudhury, its editor. The Bangladesh Today was launched in 2002. bdn
